1c - deskriptiv analys

min_df <- df %>% mutate(height_cm = Height * 2.54,
                        mom_cm=Mother*2.54,
                        dad_cm=Father*2.54,
                        parents_avg = (mom_cm+dad_cm)/2 )
ggplot(data = min_df, aes(x = height_cm)) +
     geom_histogram(binwidth = 2)

Jag fick reda pÃ¥ att R hade valt ut vÃ¤rdet 2 i fÃ¶rsta fÃ¶rsÃ¶ket.

ggplot(data = min_df, aes(x = Height, fill = Gender)) +
     geom_histogram(alpha = 0.2, position = "identity") +
     scale_fill_manual(values = c("green", "purple"))
`stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

Funktion alpha mellan 0 till 1 bestÃ¤mmer hur genomskinlig ser figuren ut

     geom_histogram(alpha = 0.5, position = "identity") +

1d - subsetta data

df_f <- df %>%
     mutate(
       height_cm = Height * 2.54,
       mom_cm = Mother * 2.54 ,
       dad_cm = Father * 2.54,
       parents_avg = (mom_cm+dad_cm)/2 ) %>%
